description:
Jack Whiting McGuire was born in Pensacola, Florida on September 13, 1905. He moved to San Antonio in 1922 and, in 1925 graduated from old Main Avenue High School. He attended the Academy of Fine Arts in Chicago, University of Texas and St. Mary's University. In 1927 he established his own schoo:: The McGuire School for Commercial Art. It was the first and largest such school in the Southwest. He maintained it until 1942.

Jack W McGuire was known for his strips Bullet Benton, Jane Arden, & The Red Knight.

He died December 30th, 1945 in San Antonio, TX.
name: Jack W. McGuire

deck: Dane DeHaan is an American actor, known for playing Harry Osborn in The Amazing Spider-Man 2.
description:
Comic Related Roles

Harry Osborn/Green Goblin

Dane DeHaan played Harry Osborn in the Marc Webb directed sequel to The Amazing Spider-Man, The Amazing Spider-Man 2.

With the death of his father, Norman Osborn, it is revealed that he is the inheritor of not only Oscorp and the Osborn fortune, but also a rare, life-threatening disease that has long affected the Osborn bloodline. In his desperate search for a cure, this leads him to ally with Electro and butt heads with Spider-Man, ultimately leading to him becoming Spider-Man's greatest foe, the Green Goblin.
name: Dane DeHaan

description:
Comic Related Roles

Harvey Pekar

Paul Giamatti portrayed comics legend Harvey Pekar in the 2003 film, American Splendor. The film was largely based on Pekar's autobiographical comic book series American Splendor, specifically, Our Cancer Year, and both real life accounts and interviews from Pekar himself. It was nominated for Best Adapted Screenplay at the 76th Annual Academy Awards.

The Amazing Screw-On Head

Giamatti voiced Mike Mignola creation The Amazing Screw-On Head in a failed animated TV pilot.

Rhino

Giamatti at long last portrayed Spider-Man villain the Rhino in 2014's The Amazing Spider-Man 2-- a character he had been wanting to play for years.
name: Paul Giamatti

deck: Well known for his work on the popular sitcom, The Office. Also for portraying Pfc. Smithson Utivich in Inglourious Basterds and Alistair Smythe in The Amazing Spider-Man 2.

Novak portrays Alistair Smythe in the Marc Webb-directed sequel to The Amazing Spider-Man, The Amazing Spider-Man 2.
